      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DAYTONA PETE (2) is a lightly raced gelding who resumes today off a long break. He's shown good ability early in his career and he'll be fitter for a recent trial. McGruddy sticks with him and this is easier than what he's been contesting in his past four outings. Can return with a bang. GIRLS DAY OUT (5) just missed in this grade last time out at Bunbury when missing out in a photo finish. Fiore hops back on board this time around and she can find the front back to 1100m. Will take plenty of catching. FANTAXTIC (4) beat home GIRLS DAY OUT last time when nabbing her right on the line. The wider draw this time around is a little niggle, but 1100m is no issue and it wouldn't surprise to see him repeat the dose. LUCKY I AM (1) is knocking on the door of another victory and the drop to 1100m may hold the key. Keep safe. SOLDIER OF GOD (6) should get every chance off the inside and can feature.",
